Henrique Faria is pleased to present Autos, Captures & Scrolls, Diana Lopez’s first exhibition in the gallery. 
SAVE THE DATE: Thursday November 9 | 6-9 pm. 

@studio.diana.lopez @by.ritual_studio

“Who really is Diana?” In a world where the act of searching for oneself and others is habitually performed through online means, the artist’s work sheds light on this contemporary phenomenon. The project, which features Diana López herself and several other women, is a unique exploration of the interplay between individual identities and the online realm. These women, with identical names but diverse roles and vocations — tattoo artist, soccer player, rock star, architect, psychologist, influencer, writer, actor, model, sex worker, Olympic athlete, and judge— are connected not by emotional bonds or professional relationships but by the shared space they occupy on the internet. Diana, as the artist, establishes the correlation among these individuals and connects them within the space of her artistic creation.

Henrique Faria is pleased to present 101dianas: Autos, Captures & Scrolls, Diana López’s first solo exhibition in the gallery. This exhibition brings together a selection of recent works in different media: video sculptures, silk screen banners, and photomurals that explore the concepts of identity and connection in the digital era.

Opens Thursday November 9 | 6-9 pm

