Marta Minujín’s first survey exhibition in the United States spans over six decades of artistic production. Minujín’s work reflects an exuberant spirit and vision infused by her intellect, humor, and performative presence. This overdue exhibition responds to a renewed interest in feminist, Pop, and Latin American art with this investigation one of their leading figures. 

The exhibition will chart Minujín’s influential career in Buenos Aires as well as time spent in Paris, New York, and Washington, DC, through a range of pioneering, mattress-based soft sculptures; fluorescent large-scale paintings; psychedelic drawings, performances; and vintage film footage. 

